text.tspan: Spiritual Warfare — By the Lord’s Victory
Days of suffering, loss, and pain,
Yet it’s now that You must gain
A true faith that would surpass
The fraught mind that tries to grasp
How such things could be allowed,
Tries to plot its own way out:
No, we shout, we praise, we soar,
For the battle is the Lord’s.
You hear us and You save
When the thunderous notes of praise
Singers shout, our voice we raise.
Rout his forces in the air;
For the battle is the Lord’s.
Ringing faith we sound in war,
For the battle is the Lord’s!
